Sentencas: The development of cathode materials, with high catalytic activity toward oxygen reduction reaction (ORR), structural stability and CO2 tolerance, is an important research direction for the successful realization of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Highly active and CO2-tolerant Sr2Fe1.3Ga0.2Mo0.5O6-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, a novel double perovskite mixed ionic conductor, i.e., Sr2Fe1.3Ga0.2Mo0.5O6-delta (SFGM), is developed by Ga-doping at Fe-sites of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (SFM) and evaluated as a cathode material in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Highly active and CO2-tolerant Sr2Fe1.3Ga0.2Mo0.5O6-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 750 degrees C, the area specific resistance (ASR) of SFGM cathode is found to be 0.099 Omega cm(2), which is similar to 50% lower than SFM cathode (0.224 Omega cm(2)) in 20% O-2/N-2 atmosphere.
Titulo: Highly active and CO2-tolerant Sr2Fe1.3Ga0.2Mo0.5O6-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, SFGM exhibits outstanding CO2 tolerance due to its excellent CO2 adsorption resistance compared with SFM.
Titulo: Highly active and CO2-tolerant Sr2Fe1.3Ga0.2Mo0.5O6-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The ASR of SFGM remains stable at similar to 0.13 Omega cm(2) during 100 h of continuous operation in 5% CO2-containing air.
Titulo: Highly active and CO2-tolerant Sr2Fe1.3Ga0.2Mo0.5O6-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, a large-sized SFGM cathode (30 cm(2)) is utilized in anode-supported flat-tube SOFCs to demonstrate the potential of SFGM in practical applications.
Titulo: Highly active and CO2-tolerant Sr2Fe1.3Ga0.2Mo0.5O6-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 750 degrees C, the as-prepared SFGM-based single-cell provides a stable power of 12 W for 291 h in 5% CO2-containing air.
Titulo: Highly active and CO2-tolerant Sr2Fe1.3Ga0.2Mo0.5O6-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The superior electrochemical performance and outstanding CO2 tolerance of SFGM are promising features for the rapid development of IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Highly active and CO2-tolerant Sr2Fe1.3Ga0.2Mo0.5O6-δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
